  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I disconnect/deactivate a postpaid connection in India? Can they come after me legally if I just break the SIM and not bother?",
  "response": "To disconnect or deactivate a postpaid connection in India, you should follow a proper procedure to avoid any potential legal issues. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to go about it:\n\n### Step-by-Step Guide to Disconnect a Postpaid Connection\n\n1. **Clear Outstanding Dues:**\n   Make sure all your bills are paid up to date. You can check your latest bill on the mobile service provider's website or app.\n\n2. **Visit the Nearest Store or Contact Customer Care:**\n   - Go to the nearest store of your service provider or call their customer care.\n   - Inform them that you want to disconnect your postpaid connection.\n\n3. **Submit a Disconnection Request:**\n   - Fill out a disconnection form, which is usually available at the store or can be sent to you via email if you're doing it over the phone.\n   - Provide your customer ID and any other details they require.\n\n4. **Return Any Provided Equipment:**\n   - If you have any equipment provided by the service provider (like a SIM card, dongle, or phone), return it to the store if they require it.\n\n5. **Get a Disconnection Confirmation:**\n   - Once the process is complete, you should receive a confirmation of disconnection. Keep this document safe for future reference.\n\n### Legal Consequences of Not Following the Proper Procedure\n\nIf you simply break the SIM card and stop using the service without informing the provider, you could face the following issues:\n\n- **Outstanding Bills:** You will still be liable for any unpaid bills. The service provider can legally pursue you for payment of any outstanding dues.\n- **Legal Action:** The service provider may take legal action against you for non-payment or for breaching the terms of the service agreement. This could result in court cases and potential penalties.\n- **Credit Score Impact:** Unpaid bills could negatively impact your credit score, which could affect your ability to get loans or other financial services in the future.\n\n### Additional Tips\n\n- **Keep Records:** Keep records of all communications and documents related to the disconnection process.\n- **Follow Up:** If you don\u2019t receive a confirmation within a reasonable time frame, follow up with the service provider.\n\nBy following the proper procedure, you can avoid any potential legal issues and ensure a smooth disconnection of your postpaid connection.",
